00_Black

Alicia received wine. It was a deep red color, as if it had
been simmered with the resentment of the victims. From that
day on, Alicia started to drink wine regularly.

Alicia's main job was to heal the tortured individuals. She
would inflict wounds, heal them, inflict wounds again, and
repeat endlessly. The techniques that were supposed to be
used as a doctor were instead utilized for efficient
torture.

Alicia experienced guilt, disgust, and despair... She had
nightmares every day, nightmares that dragged her into a
pool of blood created by the victims. However, the victims
wouldn't completely drag her into the pool of blood.

Make them suffer more, make them suffer even more. Covered
in sweat, I wake up and gulp down wine while trembling in
fear. Just as I was told, wine was the only medicine.

Several months later, the member who gave me the wine took
their own life. They chose a horribly painful death by
cutting their entire body with a knife. I considered it as
an act of repentance. Afterward, I cleaned up the corpse as
usual.

After falling into the dark ops for several years, Alicia
stopped thinking about anything. She could only live by
erasing her own identity. She didn't know the reason why she
didn't commit suicide herself.

Perhaps it was my childhood self crying out from my
unconscious. It wasn't my goal to heal people. I couldn't
completely abandon that dream somewhere.

Alicia was waiting for something. She didn't know the
specifics, but she was waiting. And then, it came in an
unexpected form.

The plan is to rescue Prince Rex from the prison. It was a
request from a member who had been dispatched as a spy from
the Senate, asking to save the severely weakened Prince Rex.

Others who were dissatisfied with the current situation, and
those who wanted to escape from the bloody place, also
agreed. In other words, it was a coup against Caron.

Alicia made an immediate decision on the request. It wasn't
that she wanted to escape from here, but rather, she wanted
to save someone. That was what she desired most.

For the sake of her childhood dream, Alicia headed towards
the person who would change her fate, Prince Rex.
